    {"id": "services_orchestrator_service_rag_schema_filtering", "label": "RAG Schema Filtering (top-K table selection)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "backend/src/services/orchestrator_service.py", "source_location": "_filter_schema_by_rag (lines 142-179)", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Embeds the user query and ranks tables by cosine similarity against precomputed table embeddings, keeping only the top-10 (_RAG_TOP_K) tables and stripping embeddings inline (no deepcopy) to keep the LLM context small on large multi-catalog schemas."},
    {"id": "services_orchestrator_service_sliding_window_history", "label": "Sliding-Window Chat History", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "backend/src/services/orchestrator_service.py", "source_location": "lines 19-20, 241-243", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Keeps the first message (which contains the schema) plus the last N=8 messages so the schema context survives while bounding token usage; LLMService additionally truncates the oldest user/assistant pair on context_length_exceeded errors."},
    {"id": "services_orchestrator_service_sql_retry_loop", "label": "SQL Self-Healing Retry Loop", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "backend/src/services/orchestrator_service.py", "source_location": "_processing_loop (lines 209-304)", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "On SQL execution failure the Trino error message is fed back to the LLM as a user turn (FIXING_SQL state) and generation is retried up to settings.MAX_SQL_RETRIES, letting the LLM repair its own queries instead of failing immediately."},
    {"id": "services_sql_generation_service_sql_sanitization", "label": "SQL Sanitization (forbidden-operation guard)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "backend/src/services/sql_generation_service.py", "source_location": "lines 16-22, 60-87", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Second line of defense after the prompt: regex-rejects DROP/DELETE/UPDATE/INSERT/ALTER/TRUNCATE/CREATE/GRANT/REVOKE/MERGE (ignoring quoted strings so literals do not false-positive), caps SQL at 10,000 chars, and normalizes trailing semicolons — only SELECT queries are allowed through."},
    {"id": "services_llm_service_proxy_failover", "label": "LLM Proxy Failover and Retry", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "backend/src/services/llm_service.py", "source_location": "__init__ / _execute_with_retry (lines 48-243)", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Supports a comma-separated list of proxy URLs, each wrapped in its own OpenAI client; on retryable errors (timeout, rate-limit, connection) it rotates to the next proxy client and retries with exponential backoff (3 attempts, base 1s), and truncates history on context_length_exceeded."},
    {"id": "services_relationship_service_fk_fallback_strategy", "label": "Foreign-Key Discovery Fallback Strategy", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "backend/src/services/relationship_service.py", "source_location": "get_relationships (lines 9-29)", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Tries the generic Trino information_schema.referential_constraints first, then falls back to DB-specific queries per connector (PostgreSQL, MySQL); ClickHouse returns empty because it has no traditional foreign keys — leaving relationship discovery there to LLM inference."},
    {"id": "docs_roadmap_mvp_v1", "label": "MVP v1: End-to-end NL2SQL on a single database", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/roadmap.md", "source_location": "lines 3-9", "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Ship a functional end-to-end NL2SQL flow on a single database first (query input, LLM orchestration with clarification turns, browser preview, Excel export, JWT auth) before adding cross-database features."},
